      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Greenwood miners union No. %\npassed resolutions expressing con-\nfidence in Charles H. Meyer, presi-\ndent, and William G. Haywood,\nsecretary. of the Western Fedora\nton of Miners. The union also\nvoted $500 to the defense fund.\n\n\nw. II. Vandusen was drowned\nlast night while trying to cross the\nmill pond on the logs of the Con-\nsolidated Lumber company at Elk.\nHe slipped and fell, and sank be-\nfore assistance could reach him.\nThe body was recovered about one\nhour later."
    }
